# Staging before production (website + bot)

Every user-facing change is verified on **staging** before **https://pokepon.org** or production bot deploy.

| | Staging | Production |
|---|---|---|
| Website | **https://staging.pokepon.org** | **https://pokepon.org** |
| Git branch | `staging` in `hamiebrooklyn.github.io` | `main` |
| Site repo | `HamieBrooklyn/pokepon-org-staging` | `HamieBrooklyn/hamiebrooklyn.github.io` |
| API | `https://api-staging.pokepon.org` | `https://api.pokepon.org` |
| Bot | `bash scripts/start-bot-staging.sh` (`:8081`) | `deploy-mac.sh` (`:8080`) |

Full setup: `docs/WEBSITE_STAGING.md` (website) and `~/Developer/Poke-Cards/docs/STAGING.md` (bot).

## Agent workflow

1. **Code** on `staging` branch (website) and in Poke-Cards (bot/API).
2. **Restart staging bot** after bot changes: `bash scripts/start-bot-staging.sh` in `~/Developer/Poke-Cards` (do not ask the user to restart).
3. **Deploy staging website** (does not touch production):
   ```bash
   cd ~/Documents/GitHub/hamiebrooklyn.github.io
   git checkout staging
   bash scripts/deploy-website-staging.sh
   ```
4. **Test** on **https://staging.pokepon.org** + staging Discord sign-in.
5. **Promote website** only when verified:
   ```bash
   bash scripts/promote-website-to-production.sh
   ```
6. **Promote bot** only when verified: `bash scripts/deploy-mac.sh` in Poke-Cards.

## Do not

- Push `main` on the website repo for feature work before staging passes.
- Use `?api=` on pokepon.org as the primary staging workflow (use **staging.pokepon.org**).
- Change production `pokepon-api-base` meta to `api-staging` on `main`.
- Tell the user to restart the staging bot — restart it yourself.

Bot staging docs: `~/Developer/Poke-Cards/docs/STAGING.md`.
